                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "For a more grounded example of what I mean, I love JS -- by default, JS has no types, and is very very Play Doh in vibe.\n\nWanting a more LEGO experience, though, over the last few years "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "url": "https:\/\/git.sr.ht\/~eli_oat\/b",
                                "text": "I’ve built up this functional programming library for JS"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " that, I think, helps to increase JS’ composability. It does this by enforcing some strict function signatures, and introducing 1 type.\n\n"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "url": "https:\/\/git.sr.ht\/~eli_oat\/b\/tree\/main\/item\/learn-b-in-y.md",
